<ns2014:section xmlns:ns2014="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.technologies.java.j2ee.ejb.enterpriseBeans.sessionBeans.stateful.introduction.whatIsStatefulSessionBean">

  <ns2015:title xmlns:ns2015="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">What are stateful session beans?</ns2015:title>
  <ns2016:para xmlns:ns2016="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    Stateful session beans maintain conversational state with the client. That is the state
    is persistent over the span of a session and across service requests. Note, however, that a
    stateful session bean is still a session bean and hence still lives only for the span of the
    client session.
  </ns2016:para>
  <ns2017:para xmlns:ns2017="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    While stateless session beans offer a services interface to clients, stateful session beans
    provide a more object-oriented approach      
  </ns2017:para>
</ns2014:section>